# ISAKMP / IKEv2 IKE_SA_INIT request (RFC 7296) over UDP/IPv4 port 500.
# CONSTRUCTED (not a live capture): assembled spec-accurately via the netkitty encoder, then verified
#   byte-for-byte against Wireshark/tshark, which dissects it fully as eth:ethertype:ip:udp:isakmp —
#   version 2.0, exchange type IKE_SA_INIT (34), flags 0x08 (Initiator), length 248, and the complete
#   SA -> KE -> Nonce payload chain (SA proposal with ENCR AES-CBC-128 / PRF-HMAC-SHA1 / INTEG-HMAC-SHA1-96 / DH group 2).
# source: netkitty codec.encode([eth,ipv4,udp,isakmp]); confirmed with `tshark -Y isakmp -V`.
#
# ISAKMP starts at frame offset 42 (eth 14 + ipv4 20 + udp 8). 28-byte fixed header:
#   1122334455667788  initiatorSPI (8)
#   0000000000000000  responderSPI (8, zero in an SA_INIT request)
#   21                nextPayload = 33 (Security Association) -> selects the first payload's type
#   20                version = 2.0 (major nibble 2, minor nibble 0 -> IKEv2)
#   22                exchangeType = 34 (IKE_SA_INIT)
#   08                flags = 0x08 (Initiator)
#   00000000          messageId
#   000000f8          length = 248 (total message: 28 header + 48 SA + 136 KE + 36 Nonce)
# Payload chain (each generic header = nextPayload(1) criticalReserved(1) payloadLength(2), then body):
#   22 00 0030 ...    SA    payload: nextPayload=34 (KE),    payloadLength=48  (1 proposal, 4 transforms)
#   28 00 0088 ...    KE    payload: nextPayload=40 (Nonce), payloadLength=136 (DH group 2 + 128B key data)
#   00 00 0024 ...    Nonce payload: nextPayload=0  (last),  payloadLength=36  (32B nonce) -> terminates the chain

